            "body": "Is this just a `\\n` vs `\\r\\n` newline thing?\n\nNote that to remove the final newline you need `:set nofixeol noeol` followed by `:w`. `:set nofixeol` is not enough if the file started out with a final newline, you need to explicitly `:set noeol` also.\n\nI can't get `echo abc = 1 > file` to produce either of the two sha256sums in the original issue, however:\n\nWith `\\n`: `78f1a1656aa4c78dbb60ac7b5d1883ac87bd79028f8e85561ba00cb0f339cf89`\nWith `\\r\\n`: `47a4a9e35796ffe622ccb505ddf43e686da583d17f55adcd34bc11d3de96aee2`\nNo eol: `61cfa85e2588a31b92d4738e77a79082db9422d7a10e2607dd2320a16b4c70b2`",
